  "text": "Expression of Yki is required, and its experimental activation, e.g. by clonal mutation of hpo, sufficient for upregulating CySC proliferation [CITATION_1] . We confirmed this also for mutations in kibra and sav: Relative to controls, homozygous kibra clones rapidly expanded ( Figure 4D ,E). The effect of clonal inactivation of sav was less pronounced in the short term but was readily detectable by increased long term retention of the clones, reflecting a reduced rate of loss from the niche [CITATION_2] (Figure S5C,D) . BrdU labelling confirmed that the expansion of the kibra clones was due to increased proliferation ( Figure S5E,F) . Homozygosity for kibra did not block differentiation, as indicated by the expression of both the CySC marker Zfh1 and the CyC differentiation marker Eya [CITATION_3] in different cells of the same clone ( Figure 4F ). Both three and five days after clone induction (ACI) the fraction of Zfh1 positive cells did not differ between control and kibra mutant clones ( Figure 4G ). As previously noted for hpo clones [CITATION_4] , the increased proliferation of the sav or kibra mutant stem cells is thus uncoupled from their ability and propensity to differentiate.",
